  "body": "*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: If I send ETH in 1-1 chat and internet connection is suddenly lost, transaction is made. Info about it I can see in Wallet but there is no message about sending ETH in chat.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nTransaction message appears in chat\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nPassword is verified, transaction is made with no message in chat history, but is mentioned in wallet\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Use Hotspot (from another device)\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Navigate to any 1-1 Chat\r\n- Send 0 ETH\r\n- Tap Enter\r\n- Tap Sign transaction\r\n- Enter you password\r\n- Turn off Hotspot\r\n- Turn on Hotspot\r\n- Check chat history\r\n- Check Wallet\r\n\r\n![lg2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36479997/36563494-4c39c56e-182b-11e8-8196-4c7e00308f82.png)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: release\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n",
